  "text": "Nanoparticles loaded with honokiol were prepared with thermosensitive poly(ethylene glycol)-poly(epsilon-caprolactone)poly(ethylene glycol) hydrogel to improve honokiol therapeutic efficacy on malignant pleural effusion-bearing mice. The hydrogel was administered intrapleurally after Lewis lung carcinoma cell inoculation. Honokiol-hydrogel reduced the number of pleural tumor foci, prolonging the survival time of MPE-bearing mice more effectively compared with the control groups. In addition, honokiol-hydrogel successfully inhibited angiogenesis as assessed by CD31 (p < 0.05). Histological analysis of pleural tumors exhibited that honokiol loaded in hydrogel led to an increased rate of apoptosis [CITATION_1] .",
